  "prompt": "How do I reset my Gmail Password?",
  "response": "To reset your Gmail password, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Go to the Gmail Sign-in Page:**\n   - Open your browser and go to [gmail.com](https://www.gmail.com).\n\n2. **Click on \"Forgot password?\":**\n   - On the login page, enter your email address and click \"Next.\"\n   - When prompted to enter your password, click on \"Forgot password?\"\n\n3. **Verify Your Identity:**\n   - Google will guide you through a series of steps to verify your identity. This may include sending a verification code to your recovery email or phone number associated with your account.\n\n4. **Follow the Instructions:**\n   - Enter the verification code you've received and click \"Next.\"\n   - Follow the on-screen prompts to create a new password. Make sure your new password is strong and secure.\n\n5. **Sign In with Your New Password:**\n   - After successfully resetting your password, you can sign in to your Gmail account using your new password.\n\nIf you don't have access to the recovery email or phone number, you may need to follow additional steps to verify your identity. The process may include answering security questions or providing other information to confirm your identity.\n\nIf you have trouble during this process, you can visit the [Google Account Help Center](https://support.google.com/accounts) for more detailed assistance.",
